msgstr "5. The training rule on mediation"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.135"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.229"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.5.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.1.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1220"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anātha­piṇḍi­"
"kassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī sāvatthiyaṃ kulūpako hoti."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Udāyī was associating with"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid "Bahukāni kulāni upasaṅkamati."
msgstr "and visiting a number of families in Sāvatthī."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid ""
"Yattha passati kumārakaṃ vā apajāpatikaṃ, kumārikaṃ vā apatikaṃ, kumārakassa "
"mātāpitūnaṃ santike kumārikāya vaṇṇaṃ bhaṇati—"
msgstr ""
"At this time, when Udāyī saw a young man without a wife or a young woman "
"without a husband, he would praise the young woman in the presence of the "
"parents of the young man,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid ""
"“amukassa kulassa kumārikā abhirūpā dassanīyā pāsādikā paṇḍitā byattā "
"medhāvinī dakkhā analasā."
msgstr ""
"“The young woman of such-and such a family is beautiful, intelligent, "
"skilled, and diligent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid "Channā sā kumārikā imassa kumārakassā”ti."
msgstr "She is suitable for your son.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "Te evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr "They would reply,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid "“ete kho, bhante, amhe na jānanti—‘ke vā ime kassa vā’ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, they don’t know who we are."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid ""
"Sace, bhante, ayyo dāpeyya āneyyāma mayaṃ taṃ kumārikaṃ imassa "
"kumārakassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"If you would persuade them to give the girl, we would take her for our son.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "Kumārikāya mātāpitūnaṃ santike kumārakassa vaṇṇaṃ bhaṇati—"
msgstr ""
"And he praised the young man in the presence of the parents of the young "
"woman,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid ""
"“amukassa kulassa kumārako abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paṇḍito byatto "
"medhāvī dakkho analaso."
msgstr ""
"“The young man of such-and-such a family is handsome, intelligent, skilled, "
"and diligent."

#. VAR: Channāyaṃ kumārikā tassa kumārakassā”ti → channo so kumārako imissā kumārikāyāti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid "Channāyaṃ kumārikā tassa kumārakassā”ti."
msgstr "He is suitable for your daughter.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid "Te evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr "They would reply,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid "“ete kho, bhante, amhe na jānanti—‘ke vā ime kassa vā’ti,"
msgstr "“Venerable, they don’t know who we are,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.15"
msgid "kismiṃ viya kumārikāya vattuṃ."
msgstr "and we would be ashamed to speak to them for the sake of the girl."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.16"
msgid ""
"Sace, bhante, ayyo yācāpeyya dajjeyyāma mayaṃ imaṃ kumārikaṃ tassa "
"kumārakassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"But if you would persuade them to ask us, we would give our girl to the "
"young man.”"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.230"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.17"
msgid "Eteneva upāyena āvāhānipi kārāpeti,"
msgstr "In this way he arranged for the taking of a bride,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.18"
msgid "vivāhānipi kārāpeti,"
msgstr "for the giving of a bride,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.1.19"
msgid "vāreyyānipi kārāpeti."
msgstr "and for marriage."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.1.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1221"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññatarissā purāṇagaṇakiyā dhītā abhirūpā hoti "
"dassanīyā pāsādikā."
msgstr ""
"At that time there was a certain former courtesan who had a beautiful "
"daughter."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "Tirogāmakā ājīvakasāvakā āgantvā taṃ gaṇakiṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr ""
"On one occasion some lay followers of the Ājīvaka sect came from another "
"village and said to that courtesan,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid "“dehāyye, imaṃ kumārikaṃ amhākaṃ kumārakassā”ti."
msgstr "“Lady, please give your girl to our boy.”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: khvayyo → khvayyā (bj, s1-3) | khvāyyo (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "Sā evamāha—“ahaṃ khvayyo, tumhe na jānāmi—‘ke vā ime kassa vā’ti."
msgstr "“Sirs, I don’t know who you are."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid "Ayañca me ekadhītikā, tirogāmo ca gantabbo, nāhaṃ dassāmī”ti."
msgstr "And I won’t give my only daughter to be taken to another village.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid "Manussā te ājīvakasāvake etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "Some people asked those Ājīvaka lay followers"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid "“kissa tumhe, ayyo, āgatatthā”ti?"
msgstr "why they had come,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid ""
"“Idha mayaṃ, ayyo, amukaṃ nāma gaṇakiṃ dhītaraṃ yācimhā amhākaṃ kumārakassa."
msgstr ""
"and they replied, “We came to ask that courtesan to give her daughter to our "
"son,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid "Sā evamāha—‘ahaṃ khvayyo, tumhe na jānāmi—ke vā ime kassa vā’ti."
msgstr "but she has refused.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid "Ayañca me ekadhītikā, tirogāmo ca gantabbo, nāhaṃ dassāmī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid "“Kissa tumhe, ayyo, taṃ gaṇakiṃ dhītaraṃ yācittha?"
msgstr "“But why did you ask the courtesan?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid "Nanu ayyo udāyī vattabbo."
msgstr "You should speak to Udāyī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "Ayyo udāyī dāpessatī”ti."
msgstr "He’ll persuade her.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.136"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1222"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid "Atha kho te ājīvakasāvakā yenāyasmā udāyī tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu;"
msgstr "They then approached Udāyī"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid ""
"“idha mayaṃ, bhante, amukaṃ nāma gaṇakiṃ dhītaraṃ yācimhā amhākaṃ "
"kumārakassa."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, we’ve asked that courtesan here to give her daughter to our son,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid "Sā evamāha—‘ahaṃ khvayyo, tumhe na jānāmi—ke vā ime kassa vāti."
msgstr "but she has refused."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid "Ayañca me ekadhītikā, tirogāmo ca gantabbo, nāhaṃ dassāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.19"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, ayyo taṃ gaṇakiṃ dhītaraṃ dāpetu amhākaṃ kumārakassā”ti."
msgstr "Would you please persuade her to give us her daughter?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1223"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.20"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī yena sā gaṇakī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Udāyī agreed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.21"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ gaṇakiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he went to that courtesan and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.22"
msgid "“kissimesaṃ dhītaraṃ na desī”ti?"
msgstr "“Why didn’t you give them your daughter?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.23"
msgid "“Ahaṃ khvayya, ime na jānāmi—‘ke vā ime kassa vā’ti."
msgstr "“I don’t know who they are, Venerable,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.24"
msgid "Ayañca me ekadhītikā, tirogāmo ca gantabbo, nāhaṃ dassāmī”ti."
msgstr "and I won’t give my only daughter to be taken to another village.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.231"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.25"
msgid "“Dehimesaṃ."
msgstr "“I know them."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.26"
msgid "Ahaṃ ime jānāmī”ti."
msgstr "Please give her to them.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.2.27"
msgid "“Sace, bhante, ayyo jānāti, dassāmī”ti."
msgstr "“If you know them, Venerable, I’ll give her.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.1.3"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.1"
msgid "Atha kho sā gaṇakī tesaṃ ājīva­ka­sāvakā­naṃ dhītaraṃ adāsi."
msgstr "She then gave her daughter to those Ājīvaka followers,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te ājīvakasāvakā taṃ kumārikaṃ netvā māsaṃyeva suṇisabhogena "
"bhuñjiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"and they took her away. For a month they treated her like a daughter-in-law,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.3"
msgid "Tato aparena dāsibhogena bhuñjanti."
msgstr "but after that like a slave."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1224"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.4"
msgid "Atha kho sā kumārikā mātuyā santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "The girl sent a message to her mother:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.5"
msgid "“ahañhi duggatā dukkhitā, na sukhaṃ labhāmi."
msgstr "“Mum, I’m unhappy and miserable."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.6"
msgid "Māsaṃyeva maṃ suṇisabhogena bhuñjiṃsu."
msgstr "For a month they treated me like a daughter-in-law,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.7"
msgid "Tato aparena dāsibhogena bhuñjanti."
msgstr "but after that like a slave."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.8"
msgid "Āgacchatu me, mātā, maṃ nessatū”ti."
msgstr "Come, mum, and take me home.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.9"
msgid "Atha kho sā gaṇakī yena te ājīvakasāvakā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the courtesan went to those Ājīvakas"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.10"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā te ājīvakasāvake etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.11"
msgid "“māyyo, imaṃ kumārikaṃ dāsibhogena bhuñjittha."
msgstr "“Sirs, please don’t treat my girl like a slave,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.12"
msgid "Suṇisabhogena imaṃ kumārikaṃ bhuñjathā”ti."
msgstr "but like a daughter-in-law.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.13"
msgid "Te evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "They replied,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.14"
msgid ""
"“natthamhākaṃ tayā saddhiṃ āhārūpahāro, samaṇena saddhiṃ amhākaṃ āhārūpahāro,"
msgstr "“We deal with the ascetic, not with you."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.15"
msgid "gaccha tvaṃ,"
msgstr "Go away!"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.16"
msgid "na mayaṃ taṃ jānāmā”ti."
msgstr "We don’t want to know you.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā gaṇakī tehi ājīva­ka­sā­vakehi apasāditā punadeva sāvatthiṃ "
"paccāgañchi."
msgstr "Being dismissed, she returned to Sāvatthī."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1225"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.18"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho sā kumārikā mātuyā santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "A second time the girl sent the same message to her mother."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.19"
msgid "“ahañhi duggatā dukkhitā, na sukhaṃ labhāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.20"
msgid "Māsaṃyeva maṃ suṇisabhogena bhuñjiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.21"
msgid "Tato aparena dāsibhogena bhuñjanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.22"
msgid "Āgacchatu me, mātā, maṃ nessatū”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.23"
msgid "Atha kho sā gaṇakī yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "That courtesan then approached Udāyī"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.24"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.25"
msgid "“sā kira, bhante, kumārikā duggatā dukkhitā, na sukhaṃ labhati."
msgstr "“Venerable, my girl is unhappy and miserable."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.232"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.26"
msgid "Māsaṃyeva naṃ suṇisabhogena bhuñjiṃsu."
msgstr "They treated her like a daughter-in-law for a month,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.27"
msgid "Tato aparena dāsibhogena bhuñjanti."
msgstr "but then like a slave."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.28"
msgid "Vadeyyātha, bhante—"
msgstr "Please tell them"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.29"
msgid "‘māyyo, imaṃ kumārikaṃ dāsibhogena bhuñjittha."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.30"
msgid "Suṇisabhogena imaṃ kumārikaṃ bhuñjathā’”ti."
msgstr "to treat her like a daughter-in-law.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.137"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1226"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.31"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī yena te ājīvakasāvakā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "And Udāyī went to the Ājīvakas"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.32"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā te ājīvakasāvake etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.33"
msgid "“māyyo, imaṃ kumārikaṃ dāsibhogena bhujjittha."
msgstr "“Sirs, don’t treat this girl like a slave,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.34"
msgid "Suṇisabhogena imaṃ kumārikaṃ bhuñjathā”ti."
msgstr "but like a daughter-in-law.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.35"
msgid "Te evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.36"
msgid ""
"“natthamhākaṃ tayā saddhiṃ āhārūpahāro, gaṇakiyā saddhiṃ amhākaṃ āhārūpahāro."
msgstr "“We deal with the courtesan, not with you."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.37"
msgid "Samaṇena bhavitabbaṃ abyāvaṭena."
msgstr "An ascetic shouldn’t get involved;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.38"
msgid "Samaṇo assa susamaṇo,"
msgstr "you should behave like a good ascetic."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.39"
msgid "gaccha tvaṃ,"
msgstr "Go away!"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.40"
msgid "na mayaṃ taṃ jānāmā”ti."
msgstr "We don’t want to know you.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.41"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā udāyī tehi ājīva­ka­sā­vakehi apasādito punadeva sāvatthiṃ "
"paccāgañchi."
msgstr "Being dismissed, he returned to Sāvatthī."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1227"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.42"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho sā kumārikā mātuyā santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "A third time that girl sent the same message to her mother,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.43"
msgid "“ahañhi duggatā dukkhitā, na sukhaṃ labhāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.44"
msgid "Māsaṃyeva maṃ suṇisabhogena bhuñjiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.45"
msgid "Tato aparena dāsibhogena bhuñjanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.46"
msgid "Āgacchatu me, mātā, maṃ nessatū”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.47"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho sā gaṇakī yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "and a second time the courtesan approached Udāyī"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.48"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and told him the same thing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.49"
msgid "“sā kira, bhante, kumārikā duggatā dukkhitā, na sukhaṃ labhati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.50"
msgid "Māsaṃyeva naṃ suṇisabhogena bhuñjiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.51"
msgid "Tato aparena dāsibhogena bhuñjanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.52"
msgid "Vadeyyātha, bhante—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.53"
msgid ""
"‘māyyo, imaṃ kumārikaṃ dāsibhogena bhuñjittha, suṇisabhogena imaṃ kumārikaṃ "
"bhuñjathā’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.54"
msgid "“Paṭhamampāhaṃ tehi ājīva­ka­sā­vakehi apasādito,"
msgstr "He replied, “When I went the first time, they just dismissed me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.55"
msgid "gaccha tvaṃ,"
msgstr "Please go yourself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.3.56"
msgid "nāhaṃ gamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "I’m not going.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.1.4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1228"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.233"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.4.1"
msgid "Atha kho sā gaṇakī ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "Then that courtesan complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.4.2"
msgid ""
"“evaṃ duggato hotu ayyo udāyī, evaṃ dukkhito hotu ayyo udāyī, evaṃ mā sukhaṃ "
"labhatu ayyo udāyī, yathā me kumārikā duggatā dukkhitā na sukhaṃ labhati "
"pāpikāya sassuyā pāpakena sasurena pāpakena sāmikenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“May Venerable Udāyī be miserable and unhappy, just as my girl is miserable "
"and unhappy because of her nasty mother-in-law, nasty father-in-law, and "
"nasty husband.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1229"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1230"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.4.3"
msgid "Sāpi kho kumārikā ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "And the girl, too, complained and criticized him in the same way,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.4.4"
msgid ""
"“evaṃ duggato hotu ayyo udāyī, evaṃ dukkhito hotu ayyo udāyī, evaṃ mā sukhaṃ "
"labhatu ayyo udāyī, yathāhaṃ duggatā dukkhitā na sukhaṃ labhāmi pāpikāya "
"sassuyā pāpakena sasurena pāpakena sāmikenā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.4.5"
msgid ""
"Aññāpi itthiyo asantuṭṭhā sassūhi vā sasurehi vā sāmikehi vā, tā evaṃ "
"oyācanti—"
msgstr ""
"as did other women who were unhappy with their mothers-in-law, their fathers-"
"in-law, and their husbands."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.4.6"
msgid ""
"“evaṃ duggato hotu ayyo udāyī, evaṃ dukkhito hotu ayyo udāyī, evaṃ mā sukhaṃ "
"labhatu ayyo udāyī, yathā mayaṃ duggatā dukkhitā na sukhaṃ labhāma pāpikāhi "
"sassūhi pāpakehi sasurehi pāpakehi sāmikehī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1231"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.4.7"
msgid ""
"Yā pana tā itthiyo santuṭṭhā sassūhi vā sasurehi vā sāmikehi vā tā evaṃ "
"āyācanti—"
msgstr ""
"But those women who were happy with their mothers-in-law, their fathers-in-"
"law, and their husbands wished him well,"

#. VAR: sukhamedho hotu → sukhamedhatu (bj, s1-3) | sukhamedhito hotu (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.4.8"
msgid ""
"“evaṃ sukhito hotu ayyo udāyī, evaṃ sajjito hotu ayyo udāyī, evaṃ sukhamedho "
"hotu ayyo udāyī, yathā mayaṃ sukhitā sajjitā sukhamedhā bhaddikāhi sassūhi "
"bhaddakehi sasurehi bhaddakehi sāmikehī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“May Venerable Udāyī be happy and well, just as we are happy and well "
"because of our good mothers-in-law, good fathers-in-law, and good husbands.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.1.5"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1232"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.1"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū ekaccānaṃ itthīnaṃ oyācantīnaṃ ekaccānaṃ itthīnaṃ "
"āyācantīnaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The monks heard that some women were criticizing him whereas others were "
"wishing him well."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.2"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "And the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.3"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī sañcarittaṃ samāpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī act as a matchmaker?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1233"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.234"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ "
"sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "The Master had the Order of monks assembled and questioned Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.7"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, sañcarittaṃ samāpajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you acted as a matchmaker?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.8"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.9"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.10"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, sañcarittaṃ samāpajjissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you act as a matchmaker?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.11"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.12"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.12a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.138"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1234"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.13"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu sañcarittaṃ samāpajjeyya, itthiyā vā purisamatiṃ purisassa "
"vā itthimatiṃ, jāyattane vā jārattane vā, saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk mediates a man’s intentions to a woman or a woman’s intentions to "
"a man, for marriage or for an affair, he commits an offense entailing "
"suspension.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1235"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs1.5.14"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.5.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.2.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1236"></a> 
#. VAR: aññatarissā → aññatarassā (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā dhuttā uyyāne paricārentā aññatarissā "
"vesiyā santike dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards a number of low-minded men who were amusing themselves in a "
"park sent a messenger to a prostitute:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "“āgacchatu uyyāne paricāressāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Please come; let’s enjoy ourselves in the park.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "Sā evamāha—"
msgstr "She replied,"

#. VAR: khvayyo → khveyyā (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "“ahaṃ khvayyo, tumhe na jānāmi—‘ke vā ime kassa vā’ti."
msgstr "“Sirs, I don’t know who you are."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "Ahañcamhi bahubhaṇḍā bahuparikkhārā, bahinagarañca gantabbaṃ."
msgstr "I already have much wealth, and I don’t want to go outside the city.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Nāhaṃ gamissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1237"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "Atha kho so dūto tesaṃ dhuttānaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "The messenger returned the message."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro puriso te dhutte etadavoca—"
msgstr "A certain man then said to those men,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "“kissa tumhe, ayyo, etaṃ vesiṃ yācittha?"
msgstr "“Why did you ask the prostitute?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "Nanu ayyo udāyī vattabbo."
msgstr "You should’ve spoken to Venerable Udāyī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "Ayyo udāyī uyyojessatī”ti."
msgstr "He’ll persuade her.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro upāsako taṃ purisaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "But a certain Buddhist lay follower said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "“māyyo, evaṃ avaca."
msgstr "“No way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "Na kappati samaṇānaṃ sakya­put­ti­yā­naṃ evarūpaṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr "That’s not allowable for the Sakyan ascetics."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "Nāyyo udāyī evaṃ karissatī”ti."
msgstr "Venerable Udāyī won’t do it.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, “karissati na karissatī”ti abbhutamakaṃsu."
msgstr "And they made a bet on whether he would."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1238"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.235"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "Atha kho te dhuttā yenāyasmā udāyī tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu;"
msgstr "Those low-minded men approached Udāyī"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid ""
"“idha mayaṃ, bhante, uyyāne paricārentā asukāya nāma vesiyā santike dūtaṃ "
"pahiṇimhā—"
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, while we were enjoying ourselves in the park, we sent a message "
"to such-and-such a prostitute,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "‘āgacchatu uyyāne paricāressāmā’ti."
msgstr "asking her to come,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "Sā evamāha—‘ahaṃ khvayyo, tumhe na jānāmi—ke vā ime kassa vāti,"
msgstr "but she refused."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.22"
msgid "ahañcamhi bahubhaṇḍā bahuparikkhārā, bahinagarañca gantabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.23"
msgid "Nāhaṃ gamissāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.24"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, ayyo taṃ vesiṃ uyyojetū”ti."
msgstr "Would you please persuade her?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1239"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.25"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī yena sā vesī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Udāyī agreed. And he went to that prostitute"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.26"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ vesiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.27"
msgid "“kissimesaṃ na gacchasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Why don’t you go to those men?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.28"
msgid "“Ahaṃ khvayya, ime na jānāmi—‘ke vā ime kassa vā’ti."
msgstr "“I don’t know them, Venerable.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.29"
msgid "Ahañcamhi bahubhaṇḍā bahuparikkhārā, bahinagarañca gantabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.30"
msgid "Nāhaṃ gamissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.31"
msgid "“Gacchimesaṃ. Ahaṃ ime jānāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I know them. Please go.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.32"
msgid "“Sace, bhante, ayyo jānāti ahaṃ gamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“If you know them, Venerable, I’ll go.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.1.33"
msgid "Atha kho te dhuttā taṃ vesiṃ ādāya uyyānaṃ agamaṃsu."
msgstr "And those men took her to the park."

#. </p><p><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.2.2"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Atha kho so upāsako ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "Then that lay follower complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma ayyo udāyī taṅkhaṇikaṃ sañcarittaṃ samāpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī act as a matchmaker for a brief affair?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1240"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa upāsakassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī taṅkhaṇikaṃ sañcarittaṃ samāpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī act as a matchmaker for a brief affair?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.139"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1241"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They rebuked Udāyī in many ways and then told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, taṅkhaṇikaṃ sañcarittaṃ samāpajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you acted as a matchmaker for a brief affair?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.9"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.10"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.11"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, taṅkhaṇikaṃ sañcarittaṃ samāpajjissasi?"
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you act as a matchmaker for a brief affair?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.12"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.13"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.13a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1242"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.236"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: itthimatiṃ → itthīmatiṃ (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.14"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu sañcarittaṃ samāpajjeyya, itthiyā vā purisamatiṃ purisassa "
"vā itthimatiṃ, jāyattane vā jārattane vā, antamaso taṅkhaṇikāyapi, "
"saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk mediates a man’s intentions to a woman or a woman’s intentions to "
"a man, for marriage or for an affair, even if just a brief one, he commits "
"an offense entailing suspension.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs2.2.15"
msgid "(<em>5</em>:<strong>9</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1243"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.4"
msgid "… pe … ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1244"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.5"
msgid "Sañcarittaṃ samāpajjeyyāti"
msgstr "Mediates:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.6"
msgid ""
"itthiyā vā pahito purisassa santike gacchati, purisena vā pahito itthiyā "
"santike gacchati."
msgstr "sent by a woman he goes to a man, or sent by a man he goes to a woman."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1245"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.7"
msgid "Itthiyā vā purisamatinti"
msgstr "A man’s intentions to a woman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.8"
msgid "purisassa matiṃ itthiyā āroceti."
msgstr "he informs a woman of a man’s intention."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1246"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.9"
msgid "Purisassa vā itthimatinti"
msgstr "A woman’s intentions to a man:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.10"
msgid "itthiyā matiṃ purisassa āroceti."
msgstr "he informs a man of a woman’s intention."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1247"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.11"
msgid "Jāyattane vāti"
msgstr "For marriage:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.12"
msgid "jāyā bhavissasi."
msgstr "you will be his wife."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1248"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.13"
msgid "Jārattane vāti"
msgstr "For an affair:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.14"
msgid "jārī bhavissasi."
msgstr "you will be his mistress."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1249"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.15"
msgid "Antamaso taṅkhaṇikāyapīti"
msgstr "Even if just a brief one:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.16"
msgid "muhuttikā bhavissasi."
msgstr "you will be in a short relationship."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1250"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.17"
msgid "Saṃghādisesoti"
msgstr "He commits an offense entailing suspension:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs3.18"
msgid "… pe … tenapi vuccati “saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr "… Therefore, too, it is called “an offense entailing suspension.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 1"

#. </h3><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.1.0c"
msgid ""
msgstr "Summary"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.5.4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.4.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1251"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.1.1"
msgid "Dasa itthiyo—"
msgstr "There are ten kinds of women:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.1.2"
msgid ""
"māturakkhitā piturakkhitā ­mātāpi­tu­rak­khitā bhāturakkhitā bhagi­ni­rak­"
"khitā ñātirakkhitā gottarakkhitā dhammarakkhitā sārakkhā saparidaṇḍā."
msgstr ""
"the one protected by her mother, the one protected by her father, the one "
"protected by her parents, the one protected by her brother, the one "
"protected by her sister, the one protected by her relatives, the one "
"protected by her kinsmen, the one protected by her religion, the one "
"otherwise protected, the one protected by the threat of punishment."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.237"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1252"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.1.3"
msgid "Dasa bhariyāyo—"
msgstr "There are ten kinds of wives:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.1.4"
msgid ""
"dhanakkītā chandavāsinī bhogavāsinī paṭavāsinī odapattakinī obhaṭacumbaṭā "
"dāsī ca bhariyā ca kammakārī ca bhariyā ca dhajāhaṭā muhuttikā."
msgstr ""
"the bought wife, the wife by choice, the wife through property, the wife "
"through clothes, the wife through the bowl-of-water ritual, the wife through "
"removing the head pad, the slave wife, the servant wife, the captured wife, "
"the momentary wife."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.4.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1253"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.1"
msgid "Māturakkhitā nāma"
msgstr "The one protected by her mother:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.2"
msgid "mātā rakkhati gopeti issariyaṃ kāreti vasaṃ vatteti."
msgstr "her mother protects, guards, wields authority, controls."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1254"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.3"
msgid "Piturakkhitā nāma"
msgstr "The one protected by her father:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.4"
msgid "pitā rakkhati gopeti issariyaṃ kāreti vasaṃ vatteti."
msgstr "her father protects, guards, wields authority, controls."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1255"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.5"
msgid "­Mātāpi­tu­rak­khitā nāma"
msgstr "The one protected by her parents:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.6"
msgid "mātāpitaro rakkhanti gopenti issariyaṃ kārenti vasaṃ vattenti."
msgstr "her parents protect, guard, wield authority, control."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1256"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.7"
msgid "Bhāturakkhitā nāma"
msgstr "The one protected by her brother:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.8"
msgid "bhātā rakkhati gopeti issariyaṃ kāreti vasaṃ vatteti."
msgstr "her brother protects, guards, wields authority, controls."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1257"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.9"
msgid "Bhagi­ni­rak­khitā nāma"
msgstr "The one protected by her sister:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.10"
msgid "bhaginī rakkhati gopeti issariyaṃ kāreti vasaṃ vatteti."
msgstr "her sister protects, guards, wields authority, controls."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1258"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.11"
msgid "Ñātirakkhitā nāma"
msgstr "The one protected by her relatives:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.12"
msgid "ñātakā rakkhanti gopenti issariyaṃ kārenti vasaṃ vattenti."
msgstr "her relatives protect, guard, wield authority, control."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1259"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.13"
msgid "Gottarakkhitā nāma"
msgstr "The one protected by her kinsmen:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.14"
msgid "sagottā rakkhanti gopenti issariyaṃ kārenti vasaṃ vattenti."
msgstr "her kinsmen protect, guard, wield authority, control."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1260"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.15"
msgid "Dhammarakkhitā nāma"
msgstr "The one protected by her religion:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.16"
msgid "sahadhammikā rakkhanti gopenti issariyaṃ kārenti vasaṃ vattenti."
msgstr "her fellow believers protect, guard, wield authority, control."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1261"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.17"
msgid "Sārakkhā nāma"
msgstr "The one otherwise protected:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.18"
msgid "gabbhepi pariggahitā hoti—"
msgstr "even when she is in the womb, there is a master who thinks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.19"
msgid "mayhaṃ esāti."
msgstr "“This is mine;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.20"
msgid "Antamaso mālā­guḷa­parik­khit­tāpi."
msgstr "and even when she is engaged for marriage."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1262"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.21"
msgid "Saparidaṇḍā nāma"
msgstr "The one protected by the threat of punishment:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.2.22"
msgid ""
"kehici daṇḍo ṭhapito hoti—yo itthannāmaṃ itthiṃ gacchati ettako daṇḍoti."
msgstr "those who punish will punish anyone going to her."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.140"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.4.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1263"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.1"
msgid "Dhanakkītā nāma"
msgstr "The bought wife:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.2"
msgid "dhanena kiṇitvā vāseti."
msgstr "after buying her with money, they live together."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1264"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.3"
msgid "Chandavāsinī nāma"
msgstr "The wife by choice:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.4"
msgid "piyo piyaṃ vāseti."
msgstr "being dear to each other, they live together."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1265"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.5"
msgid "Bhogavāsinī nāma"
msgstr "The wife through property:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.6"
msgid "bhogaṃ datvā vāseti."
msgstr "after giving wealth, they live together."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1266"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.7"
msgid "Paṭavāsinī nāma"
msgstr "The wife through clothes:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.8"
msgid "paṭaṃ datvā vāseti."
msgstr "after giving clothes, they live together."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1267"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.9"
msgid "Odapattakinī nāma"
msgstr "The wife through the bowl-of-water ritual:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.10"
msgid "udakapattaṃ āmasitvā vāseti."
msgstr "after touching a bowl of water, they live together."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1268"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
#. VAR: Obhaṭacumbaṭā → ohata … (bj) | obhata (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.11"
msgid "Obhaṭacumbaṭā nāma"
msgstr "The wife through removing the head pad:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.12"
msgid "cumbaṭaṃ oropetvā vāseti."
msgstr "after taking down the head pad, they live together."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1269"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.13"
msgid "Dāsī nāma"
msgstr "The slave wife:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.14"
msgid "dāsī ceva hoti bhariyā ca."
msgstr "she is a slave and a wife."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="51"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1270"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.15"
msgid "Kammakārī nāma"
msgstr "The servant wife:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.16"
msgid "kammakārī ceva hoti bhariyā ca."
msgstr "she is a servant and a wife."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="52"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1271"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.17"
msgid "Dhajāhaṭā nāma"
msgstr "The captured wife:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.18"
msgid "karamarānītā vuccati."
msgstr "this refers to one brought back as a captive."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="53"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1272"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.19"
msgid "Muhuttikā nāma"
msgstr "The momentary wife:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.3.20"
msgid "taṅkhaṇikā vuccati."
msgstr "this refers to a wife for one occasion."

#. </span>
#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Exposition"

#. </h4><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Mediating between a man and a single bought wife"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="54"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.4.4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1273"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.239"></a> 
#. VAR: pahiṇati → pahiṇatiṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.1"
msgid "Puriso bhikkhuṃ pahiṇati—"
msgstr "A man sends a monk, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.2"
msgid "“gaccha, bhante, itthannāmaṃ māturakkhitaṃ brūhi—"
msgstr "“Venerable, go to so-and-so protected by her mother and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.3"
msgid "‘hohi kira itthannāmassa bhariyā dhanakkītā’”ti."
msgstr "‘Please be the bought wife of so-and-so.’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.4"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhāti vīmaṃsati paccāharati, āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"If he accepts the mission, finds out the response, and reports back, he "
"commits an offense entailing suspension."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="55"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1274"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.5"
msgid "Puriso bhikkhuṃ pahiṇati—"
msgstr "A man sends a monk, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.6"
msgid "“gaccha, bhante, itthannāmaṃ piturakkhitaṃ brūhi … pe …"
msgstr "“Venerable, go to so-and-so protected by her father …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.7"
msgid "­mātāpi­tu­rak­khi­taṃ brūhi …"
msgstr "so-and-so protected by her parents …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.8"
msgid "bhāturakkhitaṃ brūhi …"
msgstr "so-and-so protected by her brother …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.9"
msgid "bhagi­ni­rak­khi­taṃ brūhi …"
msgstr "so-and-so protected by her sister …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.10"
msgid "ñātirakkhitaṃ brūhi …"
msgstr "so-and-so protected by her relatives …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.11"
msgid "gottarakkhitaṃ brūhi …"
msgstr "so-and-so protected by her kinsmen …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.12"
msgid "dhamma­rak­khi­taṃ brūhi …"
msgstr "so-and-so protected by her religion …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.13"
msgid "sārakkhaṃ brūhi …"
msgstr "so-and-so otherwise protected …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.14"
msgid "saparidaṇḍaṃ brūhi—"
msgstr "so-and-so protected by the threat of punishment and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.15"
msgid "‘hohi kira itthannāmassa bhariyā dhanakkītā’”ti."
msgstr "‘Please be the bought wife of so-and-so.’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.16"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhāti vīmaṃsati paccāharati, āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"If he accepts the mission, finds out the response, and reports back, he "
"commits an offense entailing suspension."

#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="56"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1275"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.17"
msgid "Nikkhepapadāni."
msgstr "The setting out of the steps."

#. </p><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.17a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Mediating between a man and two bought wives"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="57"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1276"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.18"
msgid "Puriso bhikkhuṃ pahiṇati—"
msgstr "A man sends a monk, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.19"
msgid ""
"“gaccha, bhante, itthannāmaṃ mātu­rak­khi­tañca pitu­rak­khi­tañca brūhi—"
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, go to so-and-so protected by her mother and so-and-so protected "
"by her father and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.20"
msgid "‘hotha kira itthannāmassa bhariyāyo dhanakkītā’”ti."
msgstr "‘Please be the bought wives of so-and-so.’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.21"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhāti vīmaṃsati paccāharati, āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"If he accepts the mission, finds out the response, and reports back, he "
"commits an offense entailing suspension."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="58"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1277"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.4.22"
