msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.14.11"
msgid "“gaccha, bhante, itthannāmaṃ itthiṃ vimaṃsā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, find out about such-and-such a woman.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.14.12"
msgid ""
"Paṭiggaṇhāti antevāsiṃ vīmaṃsāpeti antevāsī vīmaṃsitvā bahiddhā paccāharati, "
"āpatti ubhinnaṃ thullaccayassa."
msgstr ""
"If he accepts the mission, but gets a pupil to find out the response, and "
"the pupil then reports back on his own initiative, they both commit a "
"serious offense."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.15.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 3"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="187"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.4.15"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1406"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.15.1"
msgid "Gacchanto sampādeti, āgacchanto visaṃvādeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr ""
"If he fulfills the agreement when he goes, but not when he returns, he "
"commits a serious offense."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="188"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1407"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.15.2"
msgid "Gacchanto visaṃvādeti, āgacchanto sampādeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr ""
"If he does not fulfil the agreement when he goes, but he does when he "
"returns, he commits a serious offense."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="189"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1408"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.15.3"
msgid "Gacchanto sampādeti, āgacchanto sampādeti, āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"If he fulfills the agreement both when he goes and when he returns, he "
"commits an offense entailing suspension."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="190"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1409"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.15.4"
msgid "Gacchanto visaṃvādeti, āgacchanto visaṃvādeti, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If he neither fulfills the agreement when he goes nor when he returns, there "
"is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.16.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="191"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.4.16"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1410"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.16.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.16.2"
msgid ""
"saṃghassa vā cetiyassa vā gilānassa vā karaṇīyena gacchati, ummattakassa, "
"ādi­kammi­kas­sāti."
msgstr ""
"if he goes because of business for the Order, for a shrine, or for one who "
"is ill;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.16.3"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.16.4"
msgid "ādi­kammi­kas­sāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.16.4a"
msgid "5.1. Vinīta­vatthu­uddāna­gāthā"
msgstr "Case rulings"

#. </h2><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.16.4b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Mnemonic list"

#. </h5><div class="uddana"><p><a class="sc" id="192"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.16.5"
msgid "Suttā matā ca nikkhantā,"
msgstr "Asleep, and dead, gone out,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.16.6"
msgid "anitthī itthipaṇḍakā;"
msgstr "Not a woman, a sexually non-conformist female;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.16.7"
msgid "Kalahaṃ katvāna sammodi,"
msgstr "He reconciled them after quarreling,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs4.16.8"
msgid "sañcarittañca paṇḍaketi."
msgstr "And he was a mediator for sexual nonconformists."

#. </p></div><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.0a"
msgid "5.2. Vinītavatthu"
msgstr "Case details"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="193"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.144"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.5.5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.5.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.244"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1412"></a> 
#. VAR: āṇāpesi → āṇāpeti (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro puriso aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āṇāpesi—"
msgstr "At one time a man told a monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.2"
msgid "“gaccha, bhante, itthannāmaṃ itthiṃ vīmaṃsā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, please find out about such-and-such a woman.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.3"
msgid "So gantvā manusse pucchi—"
msgstr "When the monk got there, he asked some people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.4"
msgid "“kahaṃ itthannāmā”ti?"
msgstr "“Where’s so-and-so?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.5"
msgid "“Suttā, bhante”ti."
msgstr "“She’s asleep, Venerable.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.6"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi—"
msgstr "He became remorseful, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.7"
msgid "“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ,"
msgstr "“The Master has laid down a training rule."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.8"
msgid "kacci nu kho ahaṃ saṃghādisesaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno”ti?"
msgstr "Could it be that I’ve committed an offense entailing suspension?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.9"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi—"
msgstr "He told the Master, and the Master said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.10"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhu, saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa;"
msgstr "“There’s no offense entailing suspension,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.11"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti."
msgstr "but there’s an offense of wrong conduct.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.1.12"
msgid "(1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="194"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.5.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1413"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro puriso aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āṇāpesi—"
msgstr "At one time a man told a monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.2"
msgid "“gaccha, bhante, itthannāmaṃ itthiṃ vīmaṃsā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, please find out about such-and-such a woman.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.3"
msgid "So gantvā manusse pucchi—"
msgstr "When the monk got there, he asked some people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.4"
msgid "“kahaṃ itthannāmā”ti?"
msgstr "“Where’s so-and-so?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.5"
msgid "“Matā, bhante”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“She’s dead, Venerable.” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.6"
msgid "“nikkhantā, bhante”ti …"
msgstr "“She’s gone out, Venerable.” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.7"
msgid "“anitthī, bhante”ti …"
msgstr "“That’s not a woman, Venerable.” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.8"
msgid "“itthipaṇḍakā, bhante”ti."
msgstr "“That’s a sexually non-conformist female, Venerable.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.9"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.10"
msgid "“anāpatti, bhikkhu, saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa;"
msgstr "“There’s no offense entailing suspension,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.11"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti."
msgstr "but there’s an offense of wrong conduct.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.2.12"
msgid "(2–‍5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="195"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.5.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1414"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.3.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā itthī sāmikena saha bhaṇḍitvā mātugharaṃ "
"agamāsi."
msgstr ""
"At one time a woman quarreled with her husband and went to her mother’s "
"house."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.3.2"
msgid "Kulūpako bhikkhu sammodanīyaṃ akāsi."
msgstr "A monk who was supported by that family reconciled them."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.3.3"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.3.4"
msgid "“alaṃvacanīyā, bhikkhū”ti?"
msgstr "“Were they divorced, monk?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.3.5"
msgid "“Nālaṃvacanīyā, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“They weren’t divorced, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.3.6"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhu, ­nālaṃ­vaca­nīyāyā”ti."
msgstr "“There’s no offense when they’re not divorced.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.3.7"
msgid "(6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="196"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.5.5.4"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.245"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1415"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.4.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu paṇḍake sañcarittaṃ samāpajji."
msgstr "At one time a monk acted as a mediator for sexual nonconformists."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.4.2"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.4.3"
msgid "“anāpatti, bhikkhu, saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa;"
msgstr "“There’s no offense entailing suspension,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.4.4"
msgid "āpatti thullaccayassā”ti."
msgstr "but there’s a serious offense.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.4.5"
msgid "(7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="197"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1416"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss5:pts-cs5.4.6"
msgid "Sañ­carit­ta­sikkhā­padaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr "The fifth rule, the training rule on mediation, is finished."

